.TH simple_shell "1" "28 april 2023" "simple_shell(1)" "simple_shell manual page"
.SH NAME
.B simple_shell
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh
is the executable of this simple_shell
.SH DESCRIPTION
 Simple_shell program is a command interpreter that provides a simple interface for users to execute commands on a UNIX system. It reads user input from the command line, interprets the input as a command, and executes the command.

.SH OPTIONS
It supports command lines with arguments.
.B ls -l
for example.

.SH COMMANDS
The following built-in commands are supported by the \fBsimple_shell\fP:

.TP 10
.B exit
Exit the shell.

.TP
.B env
Print the environment variables.

.TP
.B cd
Change the current working directory.

.SH EXAMPLE
.B Simple_shell should work like this in interactive mode:
.br
 $ ./hsh
.br
 ($) /bin/ls
.br
 hsh main.c shell.c
.br
 ($)
.br
 ($) exit
.br
 $

.B Also like this in non-interactive mode:
.br
 $ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
.br
 hsh main.c shell.c test_ls_2
.br
 $
.br
 $ cat test_ls_2
.br
 /bin/ls
.br
 /bin/ls
.br
 $
.br
 $ cat test_ls_2 | ./hsh
.br
 hsh main.c shell.c test_ls_2
.br
 hsh main.c shell.c test_ls_2
.br
 $
.br
.SH RETURN VALUE

If the command is welled execute, the list will appear( for the command ls for example).
If it fail, an error message will be displayed.

.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
.BR sh (1),
.BR bash (1),
.BR zsh (1)

.SH BUGS

No known bugs.
Please report any issues to the authors.
.SH AUTHORS
